The evidence with the title 'Fact checking Scott Walker and unions | PolitiFact Wisconsin ' says Sep 14, 2015  ... During the heat of the battle over Act 10 , in february 2011, Walker said on NBC's " Meet The Press": "most federal employees do not have collective bargaining for benefits , nor for pay." We rated his statement True. Some federal workers have collective bargaining rights for benefits and pay , but most do not. 
